\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Rolling 36-month Sharpe ratio (minimum 12 months of data) computed as annualized mean excess return over the risk-free rate divided by annualized standard deviation. Strategy (net) in red; US Market in blue dashed; UMD factor in green dot-dash. The close co-movement of the strategy and UMD lines confirms that the strategy's performance is primarily UMD exposure.}}{10}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rolling}{{3}{10}{Rolling 36-month Sharpe ratio (minimum 12 months of data) computed as annualized mean excess return over the risk-free rate divided by annualized standard deviation. Strategy (net) in red; US Market in blue dashed; UMD factor in green dot-dash. The close co-movement of the strategy and UMD lines confirms that the strategy's performance is primarily UMD exposure}{figure.3}{}}
